Lead Analyst / Data Scientist		comScore, Inc.		US-NY-New York		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Job Description: <br /><br /><strong>Lead Analyst, Data Scientist</strong><br /><br /><strong>New York, New York USA</strong><br /><br /><strong>Reports to Vice President for Audience Analytics</strong><br /><br /><strong>Job Function:</strong><br /><br />Lead role for proficient and dedicated person with experience working with large data sets to build custom solutions in a fast paced business environment. You will analyze large amounts of data, diagnose potential issues, and design technology improvements. You’ll be improving the way we measure digital advertising campaigns. Position will require working across functional teams to trouble-shoot operational issues and build new product features and offerings. Job will require critical analysis to help solve complex problems and build custom solutions to meet external and internal demands. Self motivation is a must. Job will also require excellent communication skills with potential client interaction.<br /><br /><strong>Duties &amp; Responsibilities:</strong><br /><br /><ul><li>Work closely with software engineering, statistical services, and product management to develop new methodologies to report cutting-edge digital advertising measurement</li><li>Facilitate product operations including analyzing process and data anomalies, and fielding client inquiries. This includes working with Software Engineers, Operations, Product Support to deliver timely and quality data</li><li>Help drive process improvements, define QA processes, and integrate process enhancements into production process.</li><li>Build ad-hoc custom solutions to meet market &amp; internal needs for audience measurement reporting.</li><li>Work across functional teams to identify and resolve data issues. Apply critical thinking to quickly resolve issues. May require client interaction.</li></ul><br /><strong>Qualifications:</strong><br /><br /><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in a quantitative subject such as Statistics, Engineering, Economics, etc.</li><li>Experience in data analysis and problem solving with large amounts of data.</li><li>Experience in building methodologies and custom data solutions</li><li>Ability to think creatively to solve complex problems.</li><li>Ability to autonomously manage simultaneous projects in a fast paced business environment.</li><li>Ability to work independently and collaborate across multiple teams.</li><li>Knowledge of relational databases and methods for efficient data retrieval.</li><li>Experience with SQL Server, Hadoop or knowledge of relational databases and methods for efficiently retrieving data. Candidates with hands-on coding experience from scratch are preferred.</li><li>Experience with panel data and/or Internet behavior data a plus.</li><li>Strong Microsoft Excel skills are required.</li><li>Must have strong verbal and written communication skills</li></ul><br /><br />comScore, Inc. (NASDAQ: SCOR) is a global leader in digital measurement and analytics, delivering insights on web, mobile and TV consumer behavior that enable clients to maximize the value of their digital investments.<br /><br />Through its <strong>Audience Analytics, Advertising Analytics, and Enterprise Analytics</strong> product suites, comScore provides its clients with a variety of on-demand software, real-time analytics and custom solutions to succeed in a multi-platform world. The proprietary comScore Census Network™ (CCN) leverages a world-class technology infrastructure to capture trillions of digital interactions a month and power big data analytics on a global scale for its more than 2,000 clients, which include leading companies such as AOL, Baidu, BBC, Best Buy, Carat, Deutsche Bank, ESPN, France Telecom, Financial Times, Fox, LinkedIn, Microsoft, MediaCorp, Nestle, Starcom, Terra Networks, Universal McCann, Verizon, ViaMichelin and Yahoo!.<br /><br />EOE Statement: We are an equal emplo